"title": "5585: towers",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5585",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Tall structures, normally constructed of brick or stone. They were chiefly used for observation of the surrounding countryside in order to warn of the approach of enemies or robbers.</p>\n<h2>Examples of watchtowers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:14\">ISA 32:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:17\">JDG 8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:51-Judg9:52\">JDG 9:51–9:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:25\">1CH 27:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:7\">2CH 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:9-2Chr26:10\">2CH 26:9–26:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:15\">2CH 26:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:5\">2CH 32:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:25-Neh3:27\">NEH 3:25–3:27</a></p>\n<h3>Destruction of towers synonymous with defeat</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:4\">EZK 26:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:25\">ISA 30:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:14\">ISA 32:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:15\">JER 50:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:9\">EZK 26:9</a></p>\n<h3>Watchmen stationed in towers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:17-2Kgs9:20\">2KI 9:17–9:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:6-Isa21:9\">ISA 21:6–21:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:17\">LAM 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>Towers built as protection against thieves</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:33\">MAT 21:33</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:1\">MRK 12:1</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:1-Isa5:2\">ISA 5:1–5:2</a></p>\n<h2>Towers of Jersualem</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:9\">2CH 26:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:5\">2CH 32:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:1\">NEH 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:11\">NEH 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:25-Neh3:26\">NEH 3:25–3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:38-Neh12:39\">NEH 12:38–12:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:38\">JER 31:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:10\">ZEC 14:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:4\">LUK 13:4</a></p>\n<h2>Towers as place-names and landmarks</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:4-Gen11:5\">GEN 11:4–11:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:21\">GEN 35:21</a> <em>“Migdal Eder” means “tower of the flock”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:17\">JDG 8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:46\">JDG 9:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:51\">JDG 9:51</a></p>\n<h2>Parable of building a tower</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:28-Luke18:29\">LUK 18:28–18:29</a></p>\n<h2>Figurative use of towers</h2>\n<h3>Symbolic of the security found in God alone</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:10\">PRO 18:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps48:3\">PSA 48:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps61:3\">PSA 61:3</a></p>\n<h3>Symbolic of God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:4\">EZK 26:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:15\">JER 50:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:15-Zeph1:16\">ZEP 1:15–1:16</a></p>\n<h3>Associated with human beauty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:4\">SNG 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:4\">SNG 7:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song8:9-Song8:10\">SNG 8:9–8:10</a></p>\n<h2>The tower of Babel</h2>\n<h3>The building of the tower of Babel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:1-Gen11:4\">GEN 11:1–11:4</a> <em>The attempt to build the city and the tower is the result of human pride.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:5-Gen11:9\">GEN 11:5–11:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:9\">PSA 55:9</a></p>\n<h3>The confusion of Babel reversed at Pentecost</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:5-Acts2:11\">ACT 2:5–2:11</a></p>",
